<td width=549 bgcolor=#404040>
<font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 color=#FFFFFF>
 <br> 
 This page lists the CGF downloads. These include:
 <UL>
    <LI><B>essential downloads:</B>
    <UL>
	<LI><A HREF="#bots">CGF (bots, terrain files, missions)</A> for Action Quake2
    <LI><A HREF="#launcher">CGF Launcher</A> (by Ross 'JoeSatch' Norton)<br>
        launch missions and customize bot/player settings
    </UL>
	<LI><B>optional downloads:</B>
    <UL>
        <LI><A HREF="#weapons">additional weapons</A>
            CGF 0.80 supports 11 additional (optional) weapons, with new looks, new sounds,
            but almost identical to AQ2 balanced set of current weapons.
            <UL>
               <LI><A HREF="http://www.3ddownloads.com/showfile.php3?file_id=14695">Barrett, UZI, AK47 (by Terror Quake2 team, 4.5MB)</A>
               <LI><A HREF="http://www.3ddownloads.com/showfile.php3?file_id=14694">AK97, MAC-10, Model37, UMP-45, Dragunov, Beretta 92F<br>(by Navy Fortress team, 5.6MB)</A>
               <LI><A HREF="http://www.3ddownloads.com/showfile.php3?file_id=14693">Tommygun, old-style handcannon, 1.3MB</A>
            </UL>
 	    <LI><A HREF="#missioneditor">Borderfield's CGF Mission Editor</A> (by Incubus One)<br>
            write missions from scratch using a friendly GUI editor
        <LI><A HREF="#missions">missions</A>
            <br>
            CGF 0.80 ships with a good amount of missions; additional missions are available
            from <A HREF="./links.shtml">CGF fan sites</A>
        <LI><A HREF="#terrain">terrain files</A>
            <br>
            CGF 0.80 ships with a good amount of terrain files
    </UL>
	<LI><B>AQ2 stuff</B>
    <UL>
 	    <LI>CGF requires Action Quake2 1.51 or newer to be installed (first). Get it <A HREF="http://aq2.action-web.net">here</A>.
            Most of you have it already (and AQ2 is on the 'id extremities' CD as well).
 	    <LI>A CGF mission requires the corresponding AQ2 map (created by various members in the community)
            to be present. You only need to obtain maps for the missions you'd like to play. Most of
            you already have most maps. Go <A HREF="#terrain">here</A> to see and download them.
    </UL>
 </UL>
 <p>
 If you're new to CGF, you need to download the CGF 0.80 beta and the
 CGF Launcher files.
 <p>
 When you are already running CGF, make sure you've got the latest version
 of the CGF Launcher (1.50 or newer) and download CGF 0.80.
 <p>
 Though the 11 new weapons are optional, a number of CGF missions depends on the new weapon looks and sounds;
 I strongly suggest you download all three archives.
 <br>
 <h4>
 <A NAME="bots">CGF (bot) Binaries</a>
 </h4>
 <UL>
 	<LI><A HREF="./docs/cgf_0_81.txt">CGF 0.81 release notes</A>
	<p>
 	<LI><A HREF="http://www.3ddownloads.com/showfile.php3?file_id=14697">CGF 0.81</A> (0.9MB, Dec 25, 1999)
    <br>includes terrain files, mission, script checker (but requires launcher)
	<p>
 	<LI><A HREF="http://www.3ddownloads.com/showfile.php3?file_id=14696">CGF 0.81 upgrade from 0.80</A> (0.6MB, Dec 25, 1999)
    <br>upgrades CGF 0.80 to 0.81 with new gamex86.dll, riotx support, "SEAL" skins
	<p>
 	<LI>stand-alone script checker (part of the release)
    <br>
	<b>cgfparser.exe [Win9X/NT only, Nov 24, 1999, .zip, 69KB]</b>
	<br>
	(command line) input: the script file, <br>
	(console) output: formatted script and errors, if applicable
	<br><br>
 </UL>
 <br><br>
